Grimes says Elon Musk 'lives at times below the poverty line' and would not buy a new mattress despite her side having a hole in it
https://www.businessinsider.com/grimes-says-elon-musk-sometimes-lives-below-the-poverty-line-2022-3?utm_source=copy-link&utm_medium=referral&utm_content=topbar

Grimes told Vanity Fair that dating Elon Musk, the world's richest person, made her feel "trapped between two worlds."
Grimes 告訴浮華世界雜誌跟 Elon Musk ， 世界首富，約會讓她感覺像是被困在兩個世界之中。

Grimes said her on-again, off-again partner Elon Musk sometimes lived "below the poverty line."
Grimes  她分分合合的男朋友 Elon Musk 有時候活在 "貧窮線（聯合國定義的貧窮門檻）以下" 。 

She said Musk opted not to buy a new mattress after her side was found to have a hole in it.
她說， Musk 在她睡的那邊的床墊發現一個洞的時候選擇不購買新的床墊。

"Bro does not live like a billionaire," Grimes told Vanity Fair.
Grimes 告訴浮華世界, "歐爸活的不像是個億萬富翁" 。

Grimes said in an interview published this week that her on-again, off-again partner Elon Musk — the world's richest person — sometimes lived "below the poverty line."
Grimes 在本週出版的採訪中表示她分分合合的男朋友，世界首富， Elon Musk 有時候（生活水平像是）活在（聯合國定義的）貧窮門檻以下。

// poverty: noun [ U ] 貧困，貧窮
Two million people in the city live in abject (= very great) poverty.
這個城市有兩百萬人生活在赤貧中。

// mattress: noun [ C ] 床墊，褥墊

// despite: preposition 不管；儘管；無論
I still enjoyed the week despite the weather.
儘管天氣不好，這一周我過得還是很愉快的。

// Vanity Fair: 浮華世界 雜誌

// on-again, off-again: adjective US (UK on-off) 不連續的，斷斷續續的
The two were in a six year on-again, off-again relationship.
在六年中兩人維持著斷斷續續的關係。

// opt: verb [ I ] 選擇，挑選；（尤指）優先選擇
Mike opted for early retirement.
麥克選擇了提前退休。

// bro: noun [ C ] （稱呼男性朋友）夥計，朋友，在這裡看起來是英文的"歐巴"。
[ as form of address ] Hey, bro, what's up?
嗨，伙計，什麼事？

// billionaire: noun [ C ] 億萬富翁，擁有十億家產的人


Speaking with Vanity Fair, the musician recalled how they had once found a hole in her side of the mattress while living in Los Angeles.
在接受浮華世界採訪時，這位音樂家回憶起當他住在洛杉磯時，他們發現她睡的那一側的床墊上有個洞。

Instead of buying a new one, she said, Musk suggested that they bring over the mattress from her home instead.
她說，與其買一張新的床墊， Musk 建議(他們)從她家裡搬舊的來用。

"Like, bro wouldn't even get a new mattress," she told the publication.
"就好像歐巴甚至不會買新床墊，"她告訴浮華世界雜誌。

"Bro does not live like a billionaire. Bro lives at times below the poverty line," Grimes said, per Vanity Fair.
Grimes 對浮華雜誌說，"歐巴活的不像是個億萬富翁。歐巴有時候（生活水平像是）活在（聯合國定義的）貧窮門檻以下。"

"To the point where I was like, can we not live in a very insecure $40,000 house? Where the neighbors, like, film us, and there's no security, and I'm eating peanut butter for eight days in a row?"
"以至於我在想，我們能不能不要住在一個非常不安全的 40,000 美元的房子裡？ 就好像，鄰居偷拍我們，一點安全感都沒有。而且，(他節儉到)我連續八天都吃花生醬...@@"

// even: adverb （用來表示令人驚訝、不同尋常、出乎意料或極端的事物）甚至，連，即使
I don't even know where it is.
我甚至連它在哪裡都不知道。

// publication: noun  [ C ] 出版物
Our latest publication is a magazine for health enthusiasts.
我們最近的出版物是一本為熱愛健康人士辦的雜誌。

// at times: 有時
You can be really annoying at times, you know.
要知道，你有時很令人惱火。

// film: verb [ I or T ] 拍攝（電影）
Most of the scenes were filmed in a studio.
大多數場景是在攝影棚裡拍攝的。

// in a row: 接連地；連續地
She's been voted Best Actress three years in a row.
她已經連續三年當選為最佳女演員。


In May 2020, Musk tweeted that he would be selling all his possessions and would "own no house."
在 2020  年五月的時候， Musk  曾經發推說道，他要買掉所有的資產而且"不擁有房子"。

He is believed to be living in a $50,000 prefab tiny home, which he rents from SpaceX.
據信，他住在價值 50000 美金跟 SpaceX 租來的的小組合屋中。

Grimes also told Vanity Fair about /how dating the richest person in the world/made her feel "trapped between two worlds."
            ^^^^             ^^^^^                                             ^^^^     ^^^^            

1.把動詞介系詞劃起來 切成 三句
Grimes also told Vanity Fair about => Grimes 也告訴《浮華世界雜誌》關於..後面子句所說的事情. 
how dating the richest person in the world 和世界首富約會
made her feel "trapped between two worlds. 讓她感覺"困在兩個世界"
2.全部 => Grimes 也告訴《浮華世界雜誌》，關於她和世界首富約會如何讓她感覺"困在兩個世界"的事情。

// possession: noun [ U ] 資產
The possession of large amounts of money does not ensure happiness.
大量的財產不能確保過得快樂。

// prefab: noun [ C ] 預鑄住宅，組合式房屋
After the Second World War lots of prefabs were put up to ease the housing crisis.
二次戰後，為紓解住宅短缺的壓力而搭起了許多組合屋。

// tiny: adjective 微小的，極小的
a tiny baby
丁點大的嬰兒


"I mean, when people say I'm a class traitor that is not an inaccurate description," she said, per the outlet.
"我的意思是說，當人們說我是一個階級背叛者 (飛上枝頭當鳳凰)，這不是一個不精確的描述。" 根據她對媒體說。

*tip: 據外國朋友說， per 是相當於 according to 。
"一般会加个as, 你可能更长见到的是as per什么什么，等于according to什么什么" -- 海牛哥
outlet 則是新聞訊息的來源。
"the outlet应该是这个话的来源" -- 海牛哥

"I was deeply from the far left and I converted to being essentially a capitalist Democrat. A lot of people are understandably upset."
"我來自極左派(草根階級？)，我基本上變成了資本主義的民主黨人。很多人的不安是可以理解的。"

// traitor: noun [ C ] 背叛者，叛徒；賣國賊
The leaders of the rebellion were hanged as traitors.
叛亂的首領被作為叛國者絞死了。

// capitalist: adjective 資本主義者的
a capitalist economy/country
資本主義經濟／國家

// Democrat: noun [ C ] (美國）民主黨黨員；民主黨支持者

// understandably: adv. 可以理解的
this book offers an example of how to write clearly and understandably about the history of modern art.
這本書提供了一個例子，說明如何清晰易懂地撰寫現代藝術史

// upset: verb [ T ] 使心煩意亂；使難過；使生氣
It still upsets him when he thinks about the accident.
一想起那次事故他仍很惱火。


In the same interview, Grimes said she and Musk had a secret second child together, a baby girl they call "Y."
The couple's older son, X Æ A-Xii — pronounced "X A.I. Archangel" — was born in May 2020.
Y, whose name is Exa Dark Sideræl Musk, was conceived via a surrogate and is Musk's seventh child.

Musk told Page Six in September that he and Grimes had broken up after three years of dating.
The billionaire has recently been spotted with the Australian actor Natasha Bassett.

// conceive: verb [ I or T ] 懷孕；受孕；懷（胎）
Do you know exactly when you conceived?
你知道自己懷孕的確切時間嗎？

// surrogate: noun [ C ] 替代；代理，在這裡是說代理孕母。
For some people, reading travel books is a surrogate for actual travel.
對某些人來說，讀遊記可以替代真正的旅行。

// spot: verb 看見，看出；注意到
[ + -ing verb ] The police spotted him driving a stolen car.
警察發現他開著一輛偷來的車。


