Japan's humble birthplace of soy sauce
日本低調的醬油發祥地
https://www.bbc.com/travel/article/20220323-japans-humble-birthplace-of-soy-sauce

Soy sauce is ubiquitous throughout Japan and the world. But few know about the ancient origins of the holy grail of Japanese cuisine.
醬油在日本和世界各地無所不在。但是，這座日本料理聖杯的古老起源卻鮮為人知。

Carefully climbing the steep stairs, I followed Tsunenori Kano into the loft of the fermentation room of his family's 180-year-old soy sauce brewery, Kadocho.
小心地爬上陡峭的階梯，我隨著 Tsunenori Kano 走入家族那具有 180 年歷史醬油釀造場"角長"發酵室的閣樓。

The dark space was eerily silent except for the creaking of my steps on the old wooden boards laid between the vats of soy sauce.
除了我踩踏在醬油釀造桶古老木板上嘎吱作響，幽暗的空間寂靜地出奇。

The soy sauce was now dormant, it being late winter, but it still filled the air with a savoury aroma.
現正值隆冬之際，醬油目前休眠中(指不發酵狀態)，但是空氣中依舊瀰漫著令人愉悅的香味。

Around me, a thick, fungus-laden crust covered the ceiling, hung from the beams and grew up the walls.
環繞著我的，是一個厚實、覆蓋天花板充滿真菌的外殼。它懸掛在樑上並且爬滿了牆壁。

// ubiquitous: adjective 普遍存在的，似乎無處不在的
Leather is very much in fashion this season, as is the ubiquitous denim.
皮裝在這個季節非常流行，當然牛仔服也似乎無處不在。

