The distinctive flavour of Yuasa soy sauce reflects its ancient origins from Kinzanji miso.
湯淺醬油獨一無二的風味反映出了來它自金山寺味噌的純正血統(古代起源)。

Unlike other types of miso, which are pastes used as seasonings, Kinzanji miso is an elegant tasting, nourishing dish.
跟其他種類被當成調味醬料味噌不同的是，金山寺味噌是一道風味優雅營養豐富的佳餚。

It's a culinary relic of Song Dynasty cuisine – considered one of the world’s great developments in cooking when exquisite new tastes were created from ordinary ingredients – and has remained a popular local delicacy over the centuries, enjoyed as a snack, side dish or even light meal when added to a bowl of rice or mixed into chagayu (a porridge made from rice, water and tea).
它是宋代美食的衍伸(廚藝的遺跡) - 當從原本的食材中創造出精緻的新風味時，它被認為是世界上最偉大的廚藝發展之一 - 並且，當加入米飯或是茶粥(用米飯、水和茶煮成的粥)之中被當成小吃、配菜甚至是輕食享用的時候，這樣的吃法在過去的數個世紀中仍然是當地受歡迎的佳餚。

It was served at every meal I had while in Yuasa.
當我在湯淺的時候每餐都會吃到(被提供)。

// distinctive: adjective 與眾不同的，獨特的，特別的
a distinctive smell/taste
特別的氣味／味道

// flavour: noun UK (US flavor) （食物或飲料的）風味；（某種）味道
Add a little salt to bring out the flavour of the herbs.
加一點鹽使芳草的味道更鮮美。

