// chagayu: noun 茶粥 是關西特有的茶調味米粥。

// porridge:noun [ U ] 一般指燕麥粥，麥片粥。


As its tamari byproduct was so tasty, locals wanted a way to produce larger amounts of it.
既然壺底油是這麼的美味，當地人便想要尋求一個方法來量產它。

They efficiently adapted the Kinzanji miso-making process to create soy sauce, a thinner, yet similar tasting, form of the tamari.
他們有效率地調整了金山寺味噌製造工法來創造一種比壺底油更薄但是味道相似的醬油型態。

Established in 1841, Kadocho is one of the oldest of Yuasa's remaining soy sauce brewers; the soy sauce they produce is as close to the original type as you are likely to find anywhere in Japan.
自 1841 年建廠以來，"角長" 是現存湯淺最古老的醬油釀造廠之一。他們製造的醬油是最接近你能夠在日本任何地方找到的正宗古法釀造醬油。

As we descended from the loft, Kano walked me through the brewery and explained how the soy-sauce making process was adapted from that of Kinzanji miso.
當我們一起走下閣樓，Kano 帶著我巡視了醬油廠，並且解釋了如何從調整從金山寺味噌得到醬油的釀造工法。

Pointing out ancient wooden tools and iron equipment, he said that to make soy sauce, just two, rather than a variety, of grains, are used – steamed soybeans and toasted wheat – which are mashed rather than left whole (as is the case for Kinzanji miso) to better extract their flavour and umami.
指著那些古老的木製工具和鐵製設備，他說製造醬油只需要兩種食材 - 蒸黃豆和烤小麥 - 而不是一堆混和的穀物。它們會被研磨成泥而不是使用原來穀物的顆粒型態(金山寺味噌就是這樣[使用完整的顆粒])，這樣有助於提取食材的風味和鮮醇的滋味。

// descend: verb 下降；走下；降下
The path descended steeply into the valley.
這條路很陡，一直通到山谷。

// walk: verb [ T ] 陪（某人）走；步行送（某人）
He offered to walk her home/to the station.
他提出陪她走回家／到車站。

// variety: noun [ S ] 各種各樣；多種類型
She does a variety of fitness activities.
她參加各種各樣的健身活動。

// steam: verb [ T ] 蒸（食物）
steamed vegetables
蒸蔬菜

// toast: verb [ T ] 烤，烘
The sandwich was served on lightly toasted ciabatta.
三明治是用稍稍烤過的脆皮的義大利麵包做的。

// mashed: adjective 搗成泥狀的，搗爛的
mashed carrots
胡蘿蔔泥


They're then mixed with koji kin (green Aspergillus oryzae mould spores), as is done for Kinzanji miso, and left for three days in an enclosed room, called a muro, where the temperature is carefully controlled.
把材料跟米麴菌(綠色的 Aspergillus oryzae 麴孢子)混合在一起，就像製造金山寺味噌那樣，然後在密閉而且可以仔細溫控的房間(行業內的專有名詞稱之為 muro)留置三日。

There, the grains germinate, their starches converting into sugars, enabling fermentation.
在哪裡，穀物發芽，澱粉轉化為醣類，啟動了發酵反應。

This mash is next put into wooden barrels with copious amounts of fresh water and salt – rather than the watery vegetables used for Kinzanji miso – and the brew is fermented for at least 1.5 years to acquire the same kind of mellow, complex flavour that Kinzanji miso has.
然後把這些糊裝物放進裝有大量的清水和鹽的木桶中 -- 而不是只有跟金山寺味噌一樣加入含水量高的蔬菜 -- 而且這些釀造物會進一步發酵 1.5 年以提取金山寺味噌所特有的複雜鮮味。

// koji kin: 米麴菌

// Aspergillus oryza: 米麴菌的拉丁學名

// mould: noun UK (US mold) 黴；黴菌
There was mould on the cheese.
這塊起司發黴了。

// spore: noun [ C ] 孢子
This gave rise to a suspension of 6 million spores per 20 ml.
這產生了每 20 毫升有 600 萬個孢子的懸浮液。

// enclosed: adjective 圍住的；封閉的
He doesn't like enclosed spaces.
他不喜歡封閉的空間。

// germinate: verb [ I or T ] （使）（種子）發芽，萌芽；（使）開始生長
The beans will only germinate if the temperature is warm enough.
豆只有在溫度足夠高時才會發芽。

// starch: noun [ U ] 澱粉
Corn starch is used as a thickener in stews.
玉米澱粉在燉煮的菜餚中當作增稠劑。

// barrel: noun [ C ] UK  /ˈbær.əl/ US  /ˈber.əl/ 桶
They drank a whole barrel of beer (= the contents of a barrel) at the party.
他們在派對上喝了整整一桶的啤酒。

// copious: adjective 大量的，豐富的；過量的
They drank copious amounts of wine.
他們喝了好多酒。

// watery:adjective 含水的；充滿水的；由水組成的
a thin, watery fluid
一種稀薄而含水多的流體

// acquire:verb [ T ] 取得，獲得；購得；學到
I was wearing a newly/recently acquired jacket.
我穿著一件新買的夾克衫。

// mellow: adjective 柔和的；溫和的；芳醇的
mellow flavours
芳醇的味道


A powerful-looking man, Kano said that much of the work is done by hand.
看起來很威的 Kano 說大部分的工作都是手工完成的。

This includes regularly mixing the mash in his 34 large barrels with long wooden paddles and pressing the soy sauce from the mash when it is ready.
這些工作包括常規性的用長木槳攪拌這 34 個大木桶的食材泥以及當釀造完成後從食材泥中擠壓出醬油。

Last, Kano slowly heats the soy sauce in an iron cauldron for half a day to stop its fermentation, using pine wood for the fire.
最後 Kano 在燃燒松木的鐵釜中緩慢的加熱醬油半天以停止醬油的發酵作用。

Only about 1% of the soy sauce produced in Japan by some 1,200 companies is still made in the traditional way using wooden barrels, according to Keiko Kuroshima, a licensed soy sauce inspector and evaluator.
根據 Keiko Kuroshima (一個有執照的醬油檢查員暨評鑑者)的說法，在日本大概 1200 家公司中，只有 1% 的醬油仍然使用木桶的古早味釀造法。

One of Japan's three self-styled soy sauce sommeliers, she is the author of the definitive guide to soy sauce Shoyu Hon (Soy Sauce Book), published in 2015.
她是日本的三大侍醬油師(自己說)之一，也是 2015 年出版的醬油權威指引 Shoyu Hon （醬油書） 的作者。

// paddle: noun [ C ] （小船的）短槳，槳

// cauldron: noun [ C ] （通常指架在火上的）大鍋

// pine: noun 松樹
a plantation of pines
人工松林

// inspector: noun [ C ] 檢查員；視察員
a tax inspector
稅務稽查員

// evaluator: noun [ C ] 評鑑者

// sommelier: noun [ C ] 伺酒師
In the restaurant industry, sommeliers are often present to make food pairing recommendations for the guest.
在餐飲業，侍酒師經常在場為客人推薦食物搭配。


"Other soy sauce is mass-produced in stainless steel tanks with the aim to create a consistent taste in as short a period of time as possible, often using artificial means to accelerate fermentation," she said.
她說，"其他醬油是在不鏽鋼水槽中大量生產的，他們的目標是在盡可能短的時間區間內創造一個始終如一的口味，通常是使用人工的方法來加速發酵。"

"The wooden barrels help create a greater diversity of flavour because of the micro-organisms that live in them.
They also better reflect the skills of the brewer, their being more engaged in the process."
"木桶可以幫助創造豐富的多樣性風味，因為微生物生活於其中。
它們也比較忠實地反映了發酵者的技巧，以及他們在生產過程中更高程度的投入。"

Kadocho's soy sauce, whose flavour is characteristic of soy sauces made in Yuasa, has a thick body and powerfully rich taste, yet is pleasantly aromatic and mellow, like a well-aged cognac.
角長的醬油具有湯淺醬油的特殊風味，具有醇厚而強烈濃郁的滋味，還有就是令人愉快的芳香和濃醇，就像是一瓶陳年的干邑白蘭地。

Its flavour partly reflects Kano's use of a higher ratio of protein-rich soybeans to wheat than the industry standard.
它的風味部分地反映出了 Kano 使用了相對於小麥而言較高比例的高蛋白大豆，而這超出了該行業的工業標準。

// aim: noun 目標，目的；意圖
My main aim in life is to be a good husband and father.
我人生的主要目標是做一個好丈夫和好爸爸。

// consistent: adjective 一貫的；堅持的；始終如一的
There has been a consistent improvement in her attitude.
她的態度一直在改進。

// engaged: adjective (INVOLVED/BUSY) 捲入…的；從事…的
They've been engaged in a legal battle with the council for several months.
數月來他們一直在與市政委員會進行法律鬥爭。

// pleasantly: adverb 以令人愉快、有吸引力、友好或容易喜歡的方式
He sat there smiling pleasantly.
他坐在那裡愉快地微笑著。

// aromatic: adjective 有香味的，有香氣的，芳香的
aromatic herbs
氣味芬芳的藥草

// well-aged: adj. 陳年的

// cognac: noun [ C or U ] （產於法國西部的）科涅克白蘭地；一杯科涅克白蘭地
a bottle of cognac
一瓶科涅克白蘭地


Most brewers, even traditional ones, use a 50:50 ratio of soybeans to wheat, which produces a thinner, lighter-tasting soy sauce.
大部分醬油製造者，即使是傳統廠家，大豆比小麥的比例都使用 50:50 ，這樣生產出來的醬油口感較薄，滋味較清淡。

Kubota Soy Sauce Brewery, another old Yuasa brewer, makes two kinds of soy sauce. 
久保田釀造場，另外一家湯浅的古老業者，生產兩種醬油。

One, I was surprised to learn, is made with as much as 80% soybeans and only 20% wheat.
其一，我很驚訝地得知，使用黃豆的比例高達 80% 而且只有 20% 小麥。

The other one, matriarch Fumiyo Kubota told me, is their "light" soy sauce.
另外一種，女社長 Fumiyo Kubota 告訴我，是她們的 "淡" 醬油。

It is made with 70% soybeans and 30% wheat.
它是使用 70% 的大豆和 30% 的小麥製成。

When I stopped by, she was busy preparing koji – the mixture of koji kin and soybeans and wheat – in preparation for a new batch of soy sauce that will brew for the next 1.5 to two years.
當我路過時，她正忙著準備新一批要發酵 1.5 - 2 年的醬油要使用的米麴 - 米麴菌、大豆和小麥65的混合物。

The number of Yuasa's soy sauce brewers has dramatically declined over the last century.
湯浅的醬油釀造場在經過上個世紀之後正戲劇性的減少。

The main factor is competition from mass producers, "who compete primarily on price given the standardised quality of their soy sauce," according to Kuroshima.
主要是因為量產業者的競爭， " 他們通常在醬油已經標準化的品質上作削價競爭。 " 根據 Kuroshima 表示。

Traditionally made soy sauce is roughly two to three times more expensive than mass-produced soy sauce.
傳統釀造醬油大概比量產醬油要貴兩到三倍。

"The competition is so intense that it is not only putting the traditional brewers out of business but also mass producers in recent years," she said.
" 競爭是如此激烈以至於不是只有讓傳統釀造廠倒閉，甚至於近年來許多量產廠也活不下去了， " 她說。

// matriarch: noun [ C ] 女家長；女族長

// stop by (somewhere): phrasal verb with stop verb 順便拜訪，路過
I was passing your house, so I thought I'd stop by for a chat.
我路過你家，所以我想可以順便找你聊一會兒。

// decline: verb （逐漸）減少，衰落，降低
His interest in the project declined after his wife died.
妻子死後，他對該企劃案的興趣逐漸淡薄了。

// roughly: adverb 大致地，近似地，粗略地
We have roughly similar tastes(or roughly the same tastes).
我們的口味大致相同。

// intense:adjective 強烈的，極度的
intense cold/heat/hatred
嚴寒／酷熱／痛恨